    detail: `<p>Transport negotiation is <strong>deceptively hard</strong>. Proxies strip WebSocket headers, mobile networks drop connections, and every container has different quirks.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Automatic negotiation</strong> — WebSocket, SSE, long-polling selected per-client</li>
<li><strong>Reconnection</strong> — exponential backoff with jitter, transparent to your code</li>
<li><strong>Message cache</strong> — replay missed messages after reconnection</li>
<li><strong>Heartbeats</strong> — detect dead connections before TCP timeouts</li>
<li><strong>Proxy-safe</strong> — works behind CDNs, load balancers, and corporate firewalls</li>
<li><strong>Container-agnostic</strong> — Tomcat, Jetty, Undertow, GlassFish, Payara</li>
</ul>`,
  },
  {
