<ul>
<li><strong>Named rooms</strong> — create, join, leave with a single API call</li>
<li><strong>Presence tracking</strong> — real-time member lists, join/leave events</li>
<li><strong>Message history</strong> — configurable cache, replayed on join</li>
<li><strong>Direct messaging</strong> — send to a specific member by ID</li>
<li><strong>Authorization</strong> — accept or reject join requests</li>
<li><strong>Virtual members</strong> — AI agents and bots as room participants</li>
</ul>`,
  },
  {
    icon: `<svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
      <polyline points="16 18 22 12 16 6"/>
      <polyline points="8 6 2 12 8 18"/>
    </svg>`,
    title: 'Client SDKs for every framework',
    description: 'React, Vue, Svelte, and React Native hooks with streaming, offline queues, and auth token refresh. One API across all platforms.',
    detail: `<p><strong>atmosphere.js</strong> provides framework-native hooks so your UI code stays idiomatic.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>useAtmosphere</strong> — subscribe, push, track connection state</li>
<li><strong>useStreaming</strong> — stream AI text with progress and metadata</li>
<li><strong>useRoom</strong> — join rooms, track members, broadcast messages</li>
<li><strong>Offline queue</strong> — buffer messages while disconnected, auto-drain on reconnect</li>
<li><strong>Auth tokens</strong> — automatic refresh and session management</li>
